        <h3>The Year-wise Aggregation Logic: Decoding BCom Marksheets</h3>
        <p>A frequent search regarding **bcom online marks 2024** is about the 'Degree Completion'. For the 2024 cycle, Indian Commerce Faculties follow a strict fiscal policy threshold:</p>
        <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
            <li><strong>Part 1 & 2 Promotion</strong>: Students failing in ONE or TWO subjects are often promoted with a 'Back' or 'Supplementary' status, allowing them to clear the paper in the next year.</li>
            <li><strong>Part 3 Final Merit</strong>: The final division is determined by adding the marks of all foundational commerce subjects across 3 years. For 'Honors' students, the specialization marks carry more weight.</li>
            <li><strong>Passing Marks</strong>: Minimum 36% to 40% aggregate in each year. Professional subjects like 'Financial Accounting' and 'Corporate Audit' require deep conceptual passing.</li>
        <li><strong>Outcome</strong>: This ensures that B.Com graduates are academically and fiscally prepared for the global 'Economy' and 'Finance' competition.</li>
